      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: add exact skill version revocation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR proposes the ClawHub side of a coordinated exact-version revocation flow with OpenClaw.\n\nThe proposed contract is:\n\n- ClawHub moderators can mark one exact skill version as `revoked` or restore it to `active`.\n- ClawHub keeps the version record and audit evidence, instead of hiding or deleting the whole skill.\n- ClawHub blocks future public artifact delivery for that exact version.\n- ClawHub exposes the revocation state in the existing machine-readable bulk security-verdict endpoint.\n- OpenClaw consumes that explicit verdict in the companion PR and quarantines only installed skills whose exact version, origin, lock entry, and path all still match.\n\nCompanion PR: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/pull/90201\n\n## Why This Is Split Across Two Repos\n\nThis change needs both halves to be useful and safe:\n\n- ClawHub is the source of truth for exact skill-version revocation and artifact blocking.\n- OpenClaw is the installed-client side that can move an already-installed revoked version out of active skill loading.\n\nThe deployment order should be ClawHub first, then OpenClaw. The OpenClaw PR is intentionally defensive: if the new `revocation` field is missing, malformed, unavailable, or inconsistent, it leaves installed skills untouched.\n\n## Proposed ClawHub Behavior\n\n- Add optional `skillVersions.manualRevocation` metadata.\n- Add a moderator API path:\n  `POST /api/v1/skills/{slug}/versions/{version}/revocation`\n- Add a `clawhub-mod skills moderate-version` command for setting `active` or `revoked` with an audit reason.\n- Block revoked exact versions from ZIP download, raw-file reads, Skill Card delivery, export, and legacy package compatibility raw-file delivery.\n- Keep public API compatibility by extending `POST /api/v1/skills/-/security-verdicts` additively with:\n  `revocation: { revoked: boolean, revokedAt: number | null }`\n- Return a failed exact-version verdict with `reason: \"version.revoked\"` only when that exact version is revoked.\n- Document the moderator endpoint, the security-verdict revocation field, and the `clawhub-mod skills moderate-version` command.\n\n## Safety Properties\n\n- Revocation is exact-version scoped; other versions of the same skill remain available.\n- The version record is preserved for investigation and audit.\n- Lookup failures are not revocation signals.\n- Public API response changes are additive.\n- Existing skill-version rows remain compatible because the new field is optional.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `bun run ci:pr`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/downloads.test.ts convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts convex/skills.versionRevocation.test.ts packages/clawhub-mod/src/commands/moderation.test.ts`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/schema build`\n- `bunx tsc --noEmit`\n- `bun run --cwd packages/clawhub-mod typecheck`\n- `bunx vitest run convex/httpApiV1.handlers.test.ts packages/clawhub-mod/src/commands/moderation.test.ts`\n- `bun run format:check -- docs/http-api.md packages/clawhub-mod/README.md CHANGELOG.md`\n- `git diff --check`\n\nGoal fechado: 1,157,217 tokens, ~87m54s.\n",
